tability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'directory': ['/bin/rstats'], 'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['cna@vuldb.com'], 'url': ['https://gitee.com/WH-YHUST/tomato-rc-nvram-cve/blob/master/gitee-cve-disclosure/advisories/en/05-rstats.md', 'https://gitee.com/WH-YHUST/tomato-rc-nvram-cve/blob/master/gitee-cve-disclosure/advisories/zh/05-rstats.md', 'https://vuldb.com/cve/CVE-2026-10873', 'https://vuldb.com/submit/831866', 'https://vuldb.com/submit/831867', 'https://vuldb.com/vuln/368363', 'https://vuldb.com/vuln/368363/cti'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-10873']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-10872 - Shibby Tomato Web UI rc start_vpnserver os command injection', 'publication_date': 'Thu, 04 Jun 2026 23:16:48 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-10872', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['A vulnerability was found in Shibby Tomato 1.28.0000. This issue affects the function start_vpnserver of the file /sbin/rc of the component Web UI. Performing a manipulation results in os command injection. The attack can be initiated remotely. The exploit has been made public and could be used. This project is superseded by FreshTomato.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-10872vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-10872weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'directory': ['/sbin/rc'], 'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['cna@vuldb.com'], 'url': ['https://gitee.com/WH-YHUST/tomato-rc-nvram-cve/blob/master/gitee-cve-disclosure/advisories/en/03-start_vpnserver.md', 'https://gitee.com/WH-YHUST/tomato-rc-nvram-cve/blob/master/gitee-cve-disclosure/advisories/zh/03-start_vpnserver.md', 'https://vuldb.com/cve/CVE-2026-10872', 'https://vuldb.com/submit/831858', 'https://vuldb.com/vuln/368362', 'https://vuldb.com/vuln/368362/cti'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-10872']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2025-8873 - Arista EOS Dataplane Denial of Service via Malformed IPsec Packet', 'publication_date': 'Thu, 04 Jun 2026 23:16:48 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-8873', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['On affected platforms running Arista EOS with IPsec configured, a specially crafted packet can cause the dataplane to stop processing all IPsec traffic. The control plane may detect this condition, and attempt to reset the IPsec processing pipeline. After reset traffic may not resume being processed. There is no impact to non-IPsec traffic or to IPsec traffic not originating or terminating on the system. This issue was reported by an Arista customer.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2025-8873vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2025-8873weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['psirt@arista.com'], 'url': ['http://www.arista.com/en/support/advisories-notices/security-advisory/22869-security-advisory-0127', 'https://www.arista.com/en/support/advisories-notices/security-advisory/22869-security-advisory-0127'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2025-8873']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2024-27892 - On affected platforms running Arista EOS with OpenConfig configured, a gNMI Set request can be run when it should have been rejected (SSL Profiles Enabled).', 'publication_date': 'Thu, 04 Jun 2026 23:16:48 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-27892', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['Affected platforms running Arista EOS with OpenConfig configured, a gNMI Set request can be run when it should have been rejected. This can result in unexpected configuration being applied to the switch.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2024-27892vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2024-27892weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': [