isory/19862-security-advisory-0099'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2024-27890']}}, {'title': 'ZDI-26-331: (Pwn2Own) Microsoft Edge Feedback Log File Handling Directory Traversal Remote Code Execution Vulnerability', 'publication_date': 'Thu, 04 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0500', 'source': 'http://www.zerodayinitiative.com/advisories/ZDI-26-331/', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['This vulnerability allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code on affected installations of Microsoft Edge. User interaction is required to exploit this vulnerability in that the target must visit a malicious page or open a malicious file.', 'The specific flaw exists within the handling of feedback log files. The issue results from the lack of proper validation of a user-supplied path prior to using it in file operations. An attacker can leverage this in conjunction with other vulnerabilities to execute code in the context of the current user.'], 'observables': {}}, {'title': 'ZDI-26-330: (Pwn2Own) Microsoft Edge Navigation Handling Universal Cross-Site Scripting Vulnerability', 'publication_date': 'Thu, 04 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0500', 'source': 'http://www.zerodayinitiative.com/advisories/ZDI-26-330/', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['This vulnerability allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary cross-origin script on affected installations of Microsoft Edge. User interaction is required to exploit this vulnerability in that the target must visit a malicious page or open a malicious file.', 'The specific flaw exists within the handling of navigation. The issue results from the lack of proper validation of user-supplied data, which can lead to the injection of arbitrary script. An attacker can leverage this vulnerability to execute script in the context of a target domain.'], 'observables': {}}, {'title': 'ZDI-26-329: (Pwn2Own) Microsoft Edge Origin Validation Error Security Bypass Vulnerability', 'publication_date': 'Thu, 04 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0500', 'source': 'http://www.zerodayinitiative.com/advisories/ZDI-26-329/', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['This vulnerability allows remote attackers to access restricted functionality on affected installations of Microsoft Edge. User interaction is required to exploit this vulnerability in that the target must visit a malicious page or open a malicious file.', 'The specific flaw exists within the cross-device managed sign-in mechanism. The issue results from insufficient validation of the origin of web content. An attacker can leverage this in conjunction with other vulnerabilities to execute arbitrary code in the context of the current user.'], 'observables': {}}, {'title': 'ZDI-26-328: ASUS Business Manager Service Client-Side Authentication Local Privilege Escalation Vulnerability', 'publication_date': 'Thu, 04 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0500', 'source': 'http://www.zerodayinitiative.com/advisories/ZDI-26-328/', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['This vulnerability allows local attackers to escalate privileges on affected installations of ASUS Business Manager. An attacker must first obtain the ability to execute low-privileged code on the target system in order to exploit this vulnerability.', 'The specific flaw exists within the ASUS Business Manager Service. The issue results from the use of client-side authentication. An attacker can leverage this vulnerability to escalate privileges and execute arbitrary code in the context of SYSTEM.'], 'observables': {}}, {'title': 'Multiples vulnérabilités dans les produits NetApp (04 juin 2026)', 'publication_date': 'Thu, 04 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000', 'source': 'https://www.cert.ssi.gouv.fr/avis/CERTFR-2026-AVI-0686/', 'source_type': "['operational', 'vulnerabilities']", 'source_level': 1, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cve.org'], 'url': ['http://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2026-22054', 'http://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2026-22055', 'https://security.netapp.com/advisory/NTAP-20260603-0001', '